> These fancy-feeling flatbreads are just the pick-me-up we've been craving. We start
> by caramelizing onion with balsamic vinegar until it's deeply sweet, tangy, and
> jammy. At the same time, we roast butternut squash with aromatic thyme until
> tender and fragrant. Then, we load it all onto crispy flatbreads with creamy ricotta
> and white cheddar and bake until golden and melty. Pizza night just got a major
> upgrade.

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings). Place a
#baking sheet{} on top rack and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(thinly sliced). Dice
@butternut squash{8%ounce} into ¼-inch pieces. Strip thyme leaves from stems;
roughly chop leaves until you have 2 tsp.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #medium pan{} over
medium heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> TIP: If onion begins to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Stir in @sugar{1%teaspoon} and @balsamic glaze{1%teaspoon} (save the rest for
serving). (Use 2 tsp balsamic glaze for 4.) Cook until caramelized and jammy,
~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

While onion cooks, carefully toss squash on prepared baking sheet with a drizzle
of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, half the chopped @thyme{1/4%ounce}(chopped),
salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until tender and lightly browned,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Transfer to a #medium bowl{}; set aside. Wipe off sheet.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, remaining
chopped thyme, and @olive oil{2%teaspoon} (3 tsp for 4 servings). Season with
salt and pepper.

Lightly oil #baking sheet{} used for squash. Place @flatbreads{2} on sheet.
(For 4 servings, divide flatbreads between 2 lightly oiled sheets.)

Evenly spread flatbreads with ricotta mixture, then top with caramelized onion,
squash, and @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}.

Bake flatbreads on top rack until edges are golden brown and cheese melts,
~{10-12%minutes}. (For 4 servings, bake on top and middle racks; swap rack
positions halfway through baking.)

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and drizzle with remaining @balsamic glaze{4%teaspoon}
to taste.

Slice into pieces, divide between plates, and serve.